b'Inner Life: #ThePocketBag
.

b'The finishing touches
.
Gently brushed for softness and lustre, the cashmere is then dried, fringed and checked by hand to ensure the highest quality
.
#Burberry'

b'Woven into history 
.
Weaving takes place on complex looms, individually set up for each pattern change in a precise sequence. Once this is done, the scarves are washed in local spring water from the River Lossie, which surrounds the mill
.
#Burberry'

b'Crafted in cashmere 
.
Made at a centuries-old mill in Scotland, our cashmere scarves are dyed for up to six hours in order to create a rich and vivid colour before shades are intricately blended together 
.
#Burberry'

b'A considered approach
.
In a process that involves over 30 different steps, the cashmere is woven, washed in local spring water and carefully brushed using techniques passed down through generations
.
#Burberry'

b'A timeless icon
.
Crafted in a 200-year-old mill in the Scottish countryside, our cashmere scarves are made from the finest materials using expert methods
.
#Burberry'

b'An enduring partnership\n.\nOur cashmere scarves are an integral part of the #Burberry DNA, as is our relationship with the family-run Scottish mill who craft them \xe2\x80\x93 a partnership that started in 1900'

b'Everyone should be free to love and feel loved
.
We are proud to be a member of Stonewall\xe2\x80\x99s Global Diversity Champions programme, working with them to support LGBTQ+ initiatives around the world
.
Our donation will contribute to a range of programmes helping the LGBTQ+ community
.
#EverybodyIsFreeToLove'

b'Everyone should be free to feel safe
.
We proudly support our long-term charity partner the Albert Kennedy Trust, the national LGBTQ+ youth homelessness charity
.
Our donation will help provide safe homes, training and support to give young people the start in life they deserve
.
#EverybodyIsFreeToLove'

b'Everyone should be free to feel proud
.
We proudly support UK Black Pride, Europe\xe2\x80\x99s largest celebration for LGBTQ people of African, Asian, Caribbean, Middle Eastern and Latin American descent
.
Our donation will help support community outreach, advocacy and growth, as part of a long-term partnership
.
We are committed to helping create a truly inclusive society where everyone is respected and valued. This means confronting inequality and discrimination in all its forms
.
#EverybodyIsFreeToLove
#BlackLivesMatter'

b'We speak today as members of a global community, united in solidarity with those who are standing up for change.
.
The murders of George Floyd, Breonna Taylor, Ahmaud Arbery, Tony McDade and too many others are a painful reminder of how far we still need to go in the fight against racism and all forms of inequality.
.
As human beings, we all need to do better. If we are to build a truly inclusive society where everyone is\xc2\xa0respected and valued, we need to speak up, listen to and learn from one another and take action.
.
At Burberry, we have made a commitment to fostering a culture of inclusion, equity and belonging. Now more than ever, we stand strongly by it, informed by each other and our Diversity and Inclusion Councils.
.
As allies, we are adding our voice to the call for the change that is needed. As part of this we will be making a donation to Black Lives Matter.
.
#blacklivesmatter'

b'3/3
Burberry contributes to the fight against COVID-19.

We are donating to charities that are dedicated to tackling food poverty across the UK, including FareShare and The Felix Project. With increasing pressures on food supplies for those in need, these organisations are expanding their efforts to help those struggling as a result of the coronavirus outbreak.

Though we are apart, we stand together.

Stay safe, #StayHome.'

b'2/3
Burberry contributes to the fight against COVID-19.

We are funding research into a single-dose vaccine developed by the University of Oxford. The University has one of the world\xe2\x80\x99s best track records in emergency vaccine development, and its COVID-19 vaccine is on course to begin human trials next month.

Though we are apart, we stand together.

Stay safe, #StayHome.'

b'1/3
Burberry contributes to the fight against COVID-19.

We are using our global supply chain network to fast-track the delivery of 100,000 surgical masks to the UK National Health Service, for use by medical staff.

We are also repurposing our trench coat factory in Castleford, Yorkshire, to make non-surgical gowns and masks for patients in UK hospitals.

Though we are apart, we stand together.

Stay safe, #StayHome.'

b'Evolution of the #BurberryTrench
.
Our iconic trench coat was born from function as wartime protection. Its signature epaulettes originally displayed an officer\xe2\x80\x99s rank, while the belt\xe2\x80\x99s metal D-rings were used to attach equipment
.
Now reimagined in five distinct silhouettes named after London locations, the #BurberryTrench continues to be handcrafted in Castleford, Yorkshire
.
Cut from the gabardine fabric #ThomasBurberry invented in 1879, we are focused on sourcing 100% of our cotton more sustainably by 2022'
